= Guide -- Work Log

== Overview

A unified plain-text note-taking system for capturing decisions, meetings, observations, and status updates.
Designed for real-time capture and later reflection, with minimal friction and a programmer's aesthetic.

== Template

....
timestamp: [YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM]
title: [Title]
type: [TYPE]
---
context: [Why this matters]
insight: [What was decided, what happened, or what you observed]
rationale: [Reasoning or alternatives considered]
impact: [Who or what is affected, next steps]
tags: [#person-tag #project-tag]
....

== Types

DECISION:: High-level strategies or decisions not captured elsewhere
DISCUSSION:: Notes on discussions with key points
OBSERVATION:: Notes on interesting insights about dynamics and processes
STATUS:: Progress updates on projects and tasks

== Tips for Consistency

=== Real-time capture
* Keep the work log open during your day
* Write entries immediately after decisions or meetings -- even just timestamp and type, fill details later
* Use your editor's search to find entries quickly

=== End-of-day ritual
* Spend five minutes reviewing what happened
* Add any entries you missed
* Scan for patterns or recurring themes

=== Searching and reviewing
Use plain-text search (grep, editor search, or command line):

[source,bash]
----
grep "type: DECISION" notes | grep architecture
grep "#team" notes
grep "type: OBSERVATION" notes | grep morale
----

=== Keep a tag vocabulary
* Technical: `#architecture`, `#technical-debt`, `#process`, `#reliability`
* People: `#team`, `#person-[name]`, `#growth`, `#morale`, `#communication`
* Work: `#project-[name]`, `#hiring`, `#blocker`, `#progress`

== Examples

=== Decision

Technical or organizational choices, with rationale and impact.
Includes architectural decisions, process changes, hiring decisions, resource allocation, etc.

....
timestamp: 2026-03-13 14:30
title: Migrate authentication service to event-driven architecture
type: DECISION
---
context: Current synchronous approach causing race conditions in distributed deployments
insight: Adopt event-driven pattern with message queue
rationale:
    Decouples services, improves resilience.
    Alternative: distributed locks (more complex, slower).
    Considered async/await but team skill gap.
impact: 3-week spike, requires devops setup, affects onboarding service integration
tags: #architecture #project-authentication-service #technical-debt
....

=== Discussion

Notes on discussions that capture critical points and varying perspectives.

....
timestamp: 2026-03-13 10:00
title: One-on-one with Alex
type: DISCUSSION
---
context: Quarterly planning for direct report
insight:
    Alex wants to grow into system design; discussed Q2 projects.
    Agreed to lead refactoring of payment module as growth opportunity.
rationale: Aligns with career goals, module is high-priority, good learning opportunity
impact: Unblocks two other projects, need to schedule pairing sessions
tags: #person-alex #growth #project-payment-module
....

=== Observation
Things you notice about team dynamics, process inefficiencies, technical insights, or individual strengths.
These are lighter than decisions but worth capturing for later reflection and pattern-spotting.

....
timestamp: 2026-03-11 16:45
title: Team morale dip after missed deadline
type: OBSERVATION
---
context: Feature slipped by two weeks
insight:
    Three people mentioned frustration in standup; one person went quiet in retro.
    Visible impact on team energy.
rationale: Tied to the missed commitment we made; need to rebuild trust
impact: Schedule one-on-ones this week to check in individually
tags: #team #morale #communication
....

=== Status
Quick progress snapshots on projects, initiatives, or work streams.

....
timestamp: 2026-03-13 17:00
title: Payment module refactor
type: STATUS
---
context: Alex leading refactor; started this week
insight:
    30% complete, initial architecture review done.
    Pair sessions with senior engineer going well; no blockers yet.
rationale: On track for three-week timeline
impact: Continue current pace, monitor for blockers
tags: #project-payment-module #person-alex #progress
....
